# For CetOS
# Configuring Dynamic Ethernet client with network Manager

> nmcli con show MyEthernet     # Shows connection details
> nmcli con edit MyEthernet     # Edit connection MyEthernet
- print ipv4                    # Shows details of connection
- set ipv4.method auto          # then save and quit
> nmcli con down MyEthernet     # Shutdown MyEthernet connection
> nmcli con up MyEthernet       # Start MyEthernet connection
> nmcli con add con-name otherNet ifname enp0s3 type ethernet     # add new connection
> nmcli d
> nmcli con up otherNet         # up otherNet
> nmcli d                       # show list 
> nmcli con up MyEthernet       # up MyEthernet
